about.description:
Python is a widely used high-level, general-purpose, interpreted, dynamic
programming language. Its design philosophy emphasizes code
readability, and its syntax allows programmers to express concepts in
fewer lines of code than would be possible in languages such as C++ or
Java. The language provides constructs intended to enable clear programs
on both a small and large scale.

name: libpython-static

            - patches/0028-fix-test_macholib-for-Mac-OS-11.patch

            - patches/0030-gh21564.patch

build:

    ignore_run_exports:
        - python_abi
    number: 2
    string: hb904e53_2_cpython
requirements:
    build:
        - cctools_osx-arm64 949.0.1 h5970944_14
        - clang 11.0.0.rc1 default_hf57f61e_0
        - clang_osx-arm64 11.0.0.rc1 hd819f65_7
        - clangxx 11.0.0.rc1 default_hf57f61e_0
        - clangxx_osx-arm64 11.0.0.rc1 h43958e9_7
        - compiler-rt 11.0.0.rc1 hb5e1fa0_2
        - compiler-rt_osx-64 11.0.0.rc1 h62eb4f5_2
        - ld64_osx-arm64 530 h8c8ad8c_14
        - ldid 2.1.2 h79c402e_1
        - libclang-cpp11 11.0.0.rc1 default_hf57f61e_0
        - libcxx 11.0.0.rc1 h439d374_2
        - libllvm11 11.0.0.rc1 hf85e3d2_4
        - llvm-tools 11.0.0.rc1 hf85e3d2_4
        - tapi 1100.0.11 h879752b_0
        - zlib 1.2.11 h7795811_1009
    host:
        - libcxx 11.0.0.rc1 h3ddb984_2
        - python 3.9.0 hd001b3a_2_cpython
    run:
        - libcxx >=11.0.0.rc1
        - python >=3.9,<3.10.0a0 hd001b3a_2_cpython
test:
    commands:
        - test -f ${PREFIX}/lib/libpython${PKG_VERSION%.*}.a
        - test -f ${PREFIX}/lib/libpython${PKG_VERSION%.*}.nolto.a
        - test -f ${PREFIX}/lib/python${PKG_VERSION%.*}/config-${PKG_VERSION%.*}-darwin/libpython${PKG_VERSION%.*}.a
